\f0\b \cf2 Main findings from qualitative and quantitative research:
\f1\b0 \
1. Users\'92 main motivation for traveling is to experience something different and unique. They want to experience genuine local experiences at their destination.\
\'93I like to see and experience something different when I travel... I try to get in contact with local traditions instead of doing something that has been fabricated for tourists. Also, I like to eat local food, visit unfrequented places, and spend little time at hotels.\'94\
Survey respondents agree or strongly agree:\
91% - When I travel, I like to go beyond the ultimate touristy places\
83% - When I visit a new destination, I want to go where the locals go\
2. During their planning phase, users lack enough information from local sources about where to eat and what to do.\
3. Users plan their trips well in advance and spend most of their time deciding what activities to do.\
