\f0\b Defining a user persona based on research
\f1\b0 \
With a better understanding of the behavioral and cognitive processes of potential users, I proceeded to create a persona, which was the guiding force of ideation and prototyping.\
To further determine the scope of the problem, I created a user scenario that added specific constraints to the persona\'92s situation and goals. This scenario was part of a larger client journey map that identified feelings, pain points, opportunities. The full client journey map can download here.\'a0\

\f0\b Scenario:
\f1\b0 \
Marco is 34 years old. He is a Civil Engineer and lives in Portland, Oregon. Marco just booked his flight to Lima, Peru. Now, he is planning activities for his trip. Unfortunately, he is having a hard time finding authentic and unique experiences.\'a0\
He keeps finding the same type of activities in the different travel sites and nearly zero information about locals\'92 favorite restaurants and breweries.\'a0\
Marco is feeling deflated and fears ending up visiting all the places that are meant for tourists and miss the uniqueness of Lima.\

\f0\b Goals:
\f1\b0 \
- Having authentic and unique experiences while traveling\
- Maximizing his time and budget choosing the right things to do and places to eat\
- Staying away from tourist traps and get to discover the essence of a place through authentic food and beer\'a0 \'a0
