\f0\b \cf2 User flow diagram:
\f1\b0 \
Once I decided to commit to including a poll feature, I began defining the user flow.\'a0\

\f0\b Goals
\f1\b0 \
- Defining a critical path that allowed the user to browse through locals\'92 and travelers\'92 recommendations\
- Allowing the user to submit a poll to get current and individualized answers to his questions and review poll responses\'a0\
- Figuring out a way to keep the community sustainable by encouraging users to provide authentic information to other users\'a0\
- Reducing friction at entry-point\'a0\
Note: this user flow incorporates the task of creating an account to submit a poll. Although it can be off-putting for some users, we are assuming that our user does most of his planning on his own and way in advance. Therefore, he is used to creating accounts to manage and keep track of the information he needs for his trip. There will be wording clarifying the convenience of creating an account on the screen.\'a0\

